   "source": [
    "%pylab\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "from astropy.io import fits\n",
    "import glob\n",
    "import wget\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.style.use(['science', 'nature'])\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 250"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "70a3a558-0301-4e44-aa53-98ca1adb1c8a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Binary System Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "eb98fcb2-3889-4a39-a811-fd198bb24288",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Download Data\n",
    "First, we use wget to download the data, taking the observation data for Cen X-3 from IXPE as an example. This data has several advantages:\n",
    "- The data size is manageable.\n",
    "- It's real and publicly available.\n",
    "\n",
    "The orbital parameter provided by the GBM epoch-folding monitor (https://gammaray.nsstc.nasa.gov/gbm/science/pulsars/lightcurves/cenx3.html)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "| | |\n",
    "| --------------- | --------------- |\n",
    "| RA    | 170.3133 deg    |\n",
    "| Decl  | -60.6233 deg    |\n",
    "| Orbital Period    | 2.0869953 days    |\n",
    "| Period Deriv.   | -1.0150E-08 days/day    |\n",
    "| T half pi  | 2455073.68504 (JED)    |\n",
    "| axsin(i)    | 39.653 light-sec   |\n",
    "| Long. of periastron   | 0.00 deg    |\n",
    "| Eccentricity    | 0.0000    |\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "218ef2a4-832e-4c9b-8ae5-433d4da2f40e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "--2023-06-03 17:34:54--  https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/FTP/ixpe/data/obs/01/01006501/hk/ixpe01006501_all_orb_v07.fits.gz\n",
      "Resolving heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov (heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov)... 129.164.179.23\n",
      "Connecting to heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov (heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov)|129.164.179.23|:443... connected.\n",
      "HTTP request sent, awaiting response... 304 Not Modified\n",
      "File ‘01006501/hk/ixpe01006501_all_orb_v07.fits.gz’ not modified on server. Omitting download.\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Download the Example Data of IXPE on Cen X-3\n",
    "!wget -q -nH --no-check-certificate --cut-dirs=5 -r -l0 -c -N -np -R 'index*' -erobots=off --retr-symlinks \\\n",
    "https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/FTP/ixpe/data/obs/01//01006501/event_l2/\n",
    "!wget -nH --no-check-certificate --cut-dirs=5 -r -l0 -c -N -np -R 'index*' -erobots=off --retr-symlinks \\\n",
    "https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/FTP/ixpe/data/obs/01/01006501/hk/ixpe01006501_all_orb_v07.fits.gz"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "e68afe95-458a-48ea-a5aa-53b559aa1b57",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "01006501/event_l2:\n",
      "ixpe01006501_det1_evt2_v15.fits.gz ixpe01006501_det3_evt2_v15.fits.gz\n",
      "ixpe01006501_det2_evt2_v15.fits.gz\n",
      "\n",
      "01006501/hk:\n",
      "ixpe01006501_all_orb_v07.fits.gz\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "!ls 01006501/*"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7b2a1cee-2941-4b81-ab30-f8e47a375804",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Barycentric Correction\n",
    "Next, we use the `barycor` function from the `tatpulsar` package to apply a barycentric correction based on the solar system's center of mass.\n",
    "Please note that for IXPE data, HEAsoft has a dedicated correction program (`barycorr`).\n",
    "Here, we are demonstrate that `tatpulsar` package also includes a valid barycentric correction function."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "512b7a48-ac4b-4441-9fe2-6e9b1d54630b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "./01006501/event_l2/ixpe01006501_det1_evt2_v15.fits.gz\n",
      "./01006501/event_l2/ixpe01006501_det2_evt2_v15.fits.gz\n",
      "./01006501/event_l2/ixpe01006501_det3_evt2_v15.fits.gz\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "## READ Data\n",
    "file = glob.glob(\"./01006501/event_l2/ixpe01006501_det*.fits.gz\")\n",
    "orbit = glob.glob(\"./01006501/hk/ixpe01006501_all_orb_v07.fits.gz\")\n",
    "time = np.array([])\n",
    "\n",
    "for evt in file:\n",
    "    print(evt)\n",
    "    hdulist = fits.open(evt)\n",
    "    time = np.append(time, hdulist[1].data.field(\"TIME\"))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "0f503095-e726-47c6-88b5-b71342c6ac05",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Accelerating barycor\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from tatpulsar.utils.functions import met2mjd, mjd2met\n",
    "from tatpulsar.pulse.barycor.barycor import barycor\n",
    "\n",
    "ra=170.313301 \n",
    "dec=-60.6233\n",
    "\n",
    "tdb_mjd = barycor(met2mjd(time, telescope='ixpe'),\n",
    "                  ra=ra, dec=dec,\n",
    "                  orbit=orbit[0],\n",
    "                  accelerate=True)\n",
    "tdb_met = mjd2met(tdb_mjd, 'ixpe')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d07b0afe-3e77-4053-a44c-25a98ebea5e5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Frequency Search without Binary correction\n",
    "Next, we perform a period search for the pulsar using the `epoch_folding_search` function in `stingray`. \n",
    "\n",
    "What we demonstrate here is that the period found before applying the binary orbit correction is not the intrinsic period of the neutron star. The actual period differs from the modulated period found, due to the binary orbit modulation. \n",
    "\n",
    "However, once we apply the binary orbit correction to the photons, the period found is indeed the intrinsic period of the neutron star."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "436431f0-b69a-4717-a86e-2e1d34f69ee8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from stingray.pulse.search import epoch_folding_search\n",
    "period = 4.79660\n",
    "nbin = 64\n",
    "df_min = 1e-4\n",
    "df = 1e-5\n",
    "frequencies = np.arange(1/period - 1e-3, 1/period + 1e-3, df)\n",
    "\n",
    "freq, efstat = epoch_folding_search(tdb_met, frequencies, nbin=nbin)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "851227a1-c6c0-42ec-88fc-f68e62aeffeb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x7f9e5dbd5210>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 825x625 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 250\n",
    "plt.figure()\n",
    "plt.plot(freq, efstat)\n",
    "plt.axhline(nbin -1, ls='--', lw=3, color='k', label='n-1')\n",
    "plt.axvline(1/period, lw=3, alpha=0.5, color='r', label='True frequency')\n",
    "plt.axvline(freq[np.argmax(efstat)], lw=3, alpha=0.5, color='k', label='Observed frequency')\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Freq (Hz)\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"EF stat\")\n",
    "plt.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b05d7f41-43e9-4acd-8e4a-8aa34e7815c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Binary Correction\n",
    "Next, we apply a binary orbit correction using two methods. One is the correction under extreme gravitational fields as described in Deeter's paper, and the other is by solving Kepler's equation to calculate the intrinsic emission time of the photons in the binary system."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "eabd8f2e-c169-4502-939a-090953ac8fb2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Deeter correction \n",
    "Correct the photon arrival times to the photon emission time Deeter model.\n",
    "\n",
    "Reference: `Deeter et al. 1981, ApJ, 247:1003-1012`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "ec0240d1-67ba-4c58-bbe7-bce8dfb69faf",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x7f9e5e060a10>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 825x625 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from tatpulsar.pulse.binary import orbit_cor_deeter\n",
    "\n",
    "#-----------------------------------\n",
    "Porb = 2.0869953 #day\n",
    "axsini = 39.653 #light-sec\n",
    "e = 0.0000\n",
    "omega = 0.00 - np.pi/2\n",
    "T_pi2 = 2455073.68504 - 2400000.5 #mjd \n",
    "x_mid = 298\n",
    "y_mid = 306\n",
    "\n",
    "Tnod = T_pi2 + Porb/2 # mjd\n",
    "tnod = mjd2met(Tnod, telescope='ixpe') #met\n",
    "\n",
    "tdb_bicor = orbit_cor_deeter(tdb_met, Porb*86400, axsini, e, omega, tnod)\n",
    "    \n",
    "## EF search\n",
    "period = 4.79660\n",
    "nbin = 16\n",
    "df_min = 1e-4\n",
    "df = 1e-6\n",
    "frequencies = np.arange(1/period- 1e-3, 1/period + 1e-3, df)\n",
    "freq, efstat = epoch_folding_search(tdb_bicor, frequencies, nbin=nbin)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plotting\n",
    "plt.plot(freq, efstat)\n",
    "plt.axhline(nbin -1, ls='--', lw=3, color='k', label='n-1')\n",
    "plt.axvline(1/period, lw=3, alpha=0.5, color='black', label='True frequency')\n",
    "plt.axvline(freq[np.argmax(efstat)], lw=3, alpha=0.5, color='r', label='Observed frequency')\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Freq (Hz)\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"EF stat\")\n",
    "plt.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "80725d36-f431-4a9f-b355-9b939ac85364",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Solving Kepler equation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "8ca3f600-d5af-4e51-8d62-816b01ae6b7d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from tatpulsar.pulse.binary import orbit_cor_kepler"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "7bdc237d-4b81-4561-b7f4-9ae898a60376",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Help on function orbit_cor_kepler in module tatpulsar.pulse.binary:\n",
      "\n",
      "orbit_cor_kepler(time, Tw, ecc, Porb, omega, axsini, PdotOrb=0, omegadot=0, gamma=0)\n",
      "    Corrects observed times of photons to their emission times\n",
      "    based on the Kepler function for a binary system.\n",
      "    \n",
      "    Parameters\n",
      "    ----------\n",
      "    time: float\n",
      "        The time of observed photon in MJD\n",
      "    Tw: float\n",
      "        The periastron time in MJD\n",
      "    ecc: float\n",
      "        Eccentricity\n",
      "    Porb: float\n",
      "        Orbital period in second\n",
      "    PdotOrb: float (optional)\n",
      "        Second derivative of Orbital period in sec/sec default is 0\n",
      "    omega: float\n",
      "        Long. of periastron in radians.\n",
      "    omegadot: float (optional)\n",
      "        second derivative of Long. of periastron in rad/sec\n",
      "    axsini: float\n",
      "        projection of semi major axis in light-sec\n",
      "    gamma: float\n",
      "        0\n",
      "    \n",
      "    Returns\n",
      "    -------\n",
      "    t_em: float\n",
      "        The emitting time of photon in binary system in MJD\n",
      "    \n",
      "    Example\n",
      "    -------\n",
      "    >>> observed_time = np.array([...]) # Time series in MJD\n",
      "    >>> Tw = 54424.71               #Barycentric time (in MJD(TDB)) of periastron\n",
      "    >>> e = 0.68                    #orbital eccentricity\n",
      "    >>> Porb = 249.48 * 86400.      #Orbital period (s)\n",
      "    >>> omega = -26. *np.pi/180.    #Longitude of periastron (radians)\n",
      "    >>> axsin = 530.                 #Projected semi-major axis (light seconds)\n",
      "    >>> Porb_dot = 0                #First derivative of Orbital period\n",
      "    >>> binary_corrected_time = orbit_cor_kepler(observed_time\n",
      "                                                Tw=Tw,\n",
      "                                                ecc=e,\n",
      "                                                Porb=Porb,\n",
      "                                                Porb_dot,\n",
      "                                                omega,\n",
      "                                                0,\n",
      "                                                asin,\n",
      "                                                0)\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "help(orbit_cor_kepler)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "id": "0a16f571-72c8-4499-b827-41e9a079531f",
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "#-----------------------------------\n",

    "axsini = 39.653 #light-sec\n",
    "e = 0.0000\n",
    "omega = 0.00 - np.pi/2\n",
    "T_pi2 = 2455073.68504 - 2400000.5 #mjd \n",
    "\n",
    "T_periastron = T_pi2 + Porb/2 # mjd\n",

    "                                    Porb=Porb*86400,\n",

    "                                    axsini=axsini)\n",
    "tdb_bicor_kepler = mjd2met(tdb_bicor_kepler, 'ixpe')"
   ]
